Birula, 1900
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD9FFB59458FC5FFC39FAF2" blockId="2.[830,1441,904,1326]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59458FC5FFC3FFC43" box="[830,938,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Dorsal trichobothria of femur arranged in 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59458FC70FCF9FC62" box="[830,876,935,958]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">beta</emphasis>
configuration. Trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59387FC70FB62FC1C" box="[1249,1271,935,960]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">
d 
<subScript id="17FC34F8FFD9FFB59388FC66FB62FC1C" attach="left" box="[1262,1271,945,960]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">3</subScript>
</emphasis>
on patella is located dorsally from 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59350FC11FBFDFC03" box="[1078,1128,966,991]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">
<subScript id="17FC34F8FFD9FFB59350FC11FBFDFC03" attach="left" box="[1078,1128,966,991]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">DMc</subScript>
</emphasis>
carina. Tibial spurs present on legs III and IV. Cheliceral fixed finger with two ventral denticles. Carapace with distinct carinae (
<figureCitation id="13432A38FFD9FFB59237FBD4FA07FBC6" box="[1361,1426,1027,1050]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="6.[192,268,974,997]" captionTargetBox="[189,1442,202,939]" captionTargetId="figure-7@6.[192,1439,205,936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 6: Sassanidotus gracilis (Birula, 1900), female holotype, dorsal aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4649004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4649004/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), in lateral view with entire dorsal surface horizontal or almost horizontal. Central median and posterior median carinae of carapace fused into one linear carina. Movable finger of pedipalp with three granules located proximally to the terminal granule. Trichobothrium 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB592E3FB4BFA35FB6F" box="[1413,1440,1180,1203]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">db</emphasis>
on chela of pedipalp closer to 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB593E5FB6CFB33FB0E" box="[1155,1190,1211,1234]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">esb</emphasis>
or as far as 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB5924CFB6CFADDFB0E" box="[1322,1352,1211,1234]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">est</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13432A38FFD9FFB59230FB6CFC11FB2D" captionStart="Figures 1–2" captionStartId="3.[875,961,1083,1106]" captionTargetBox="[211,808,183,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-8@3.[192,851,168,1199]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1–2: Chela of pedipalp showing external trichobothria. 1. Sassanidotus zarudnyi (Birula, 1900), male neotype. 2. Sassanidotus gracilis (Birula, 1900), female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648995/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Figs. 1 and 2</figureCitation>
). Tergites I–VI tricarinate. Carinae of tergites projecting beyond posterior margin as distinct spiniform processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD9FFB59458FAB0FC11F985" blockId="2.[830,1441,1383,1901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59458FAB0FC3AFAA2" box="[830,943,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Comments</emphasis>
: The description of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB59273FAB0FA35FAA2" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1301,1440,1383,1406]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59273FAB0FA35FAA2" box="[1301,1440,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was published in a book by Farzanpay (1987: 161) in Farsi, and the Latin name was transliterated in the Farsi text as well. The Index in this book, however, included Latin names (p. 221, 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB5934CFA33FB20FA27" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1066,1205,1508,1531]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB5934CFA33FB20FA27" box="[1066,1205,1508,1531]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the original spelling with “t”, not “th”), which technically makes this name available under Farzanpay’s authorship (Fet &amp; Lowe, 2000).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD9FFB49408F9B6FD8BF9D0" blockId="2.[830,1441,1383,1901]" lastBlockId="3.[192,802,1218,1916]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">
The single species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB5933DF9B6FA35F9A4" authority="Farzanpay, 1987" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1115,1440,1633,1656]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB5933DF9B6FB70F9A4" box="[1115,1253,1633,1656]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
Farzanpay, 1987
</taxonomicName>
listed by Fet &amp; Lowe (2000) was formerly placed in the genera 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB594F5F949FBE3F969" authority="Leach, 1815" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[915,1142,1694,1717]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB594F5F949FC48F969" box="[915,989,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Buthus</emphasis>
Leach, 1815
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB593DEF949FCE6F908" authority="Vachon, 1950" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB593DEF949FAACF969" box="[1208,1337,1694,1717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Mesobuthus</emphasis>
Vachon, 1950
</taxonomicName>
. In our opinion, 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB5932EF96AFB46F908" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1096,1235,1725,1748]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB5932EF96AFB46F908" box="[1096,1235,1725,1748]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid genus closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB59374F90BFACEF92F" authority="Vachon, 1949" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1949" box="[1042,1371,1756,1779]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Compsobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59374F90BFB24F92F" box="[1042,1201,1756,1779]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Compsobuthus</emphasis>
Vachon, 1949
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares most of the characters noted in the diagnosis above including the shape of carinae on the carapace. The main diagnostic difference is that 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD9FFB59458F881FC5CF8B1" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[830,969,1878,1901]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="2" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD9FFB59458F881FC5CF8B1" box="[830,969,1878,1901]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="1">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has only three granules located proximally to the terminal granule on the movable finger of pedipalp (fig. 
<quantity id="4C809B58FFD8FFB49631FB36FE18FB24" box="[343,397,1249,1272]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.604" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="26.0">26 in</quantity>
Vachon, 1958: 143), whereas species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49797FB28FE05FACA" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1949" box="[241,400,1279,1302]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Compsobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49797FB28FE05FACA" box="[241,400,1279,1302]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Compsobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and also 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB4956FFB28FD1FFACA" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[521,650,1279,1302]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4956FFB28FD1FFACA" box="[521,650,1279,1302]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mesobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
always have four such granules (fig. 
<quantity id="4C809B58FFD8FFB496AEFAC9FD94FAE9" box="[456,513,1310,1333]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.858" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="27.0">27 in</quantity>
Vachon, 1958: 143). This diagnostic character, first observed by Vachon (1958), was repeated by Farzanpay (1987: 161) in his brief Farsi description and key. Vachon (1958: 143–145, figs. 26– 27) first suggested that the species originally known as 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB497A6FA60FD98FA12" authority="Birula, 1900" authorityName="Birula" authorityYear="1900" box="[192,525,1463,1486]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zarudnyi">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB497A6FA60FEE1FA12" box="[192,372,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthus zarudnyi</emphasis>
Birula, 1900
</taxonomicName>
does not belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49677FA01FE07FA31" authorityName="Vachon" authorityYear="1950" box="[273,402,1494,1517]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Mesobuthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49677FA01FE07FA31" box="[273,402,1494,1517]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Mesobuthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where it was previously placed (Vachon, 1950: 153; 1952: 325).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF076635FFD8FFB4940DFBECFB99FB40" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648995" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4648995" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648995/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" startId="3.[875,961,1083,1106]" targetBox="[211,808,183,1175]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD8FFB4940DFBECFB99FB40" blockId="3.[875,1440,1083,1180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4940DFBECFB90FB8E" bold="true" box="[875,1029,1083,1106]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Figures 1–2:</emphasis>
Chela of pedipalp showing external trichobothria. 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4949DFB81FB9BFBB7" bold="true" box="[1019,1038,1110,1131]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB4937DFB81FA09FBB7" authority="(Birula, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Birula" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1051,1436,1110,1131]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zarudnyi">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4937DFB81FB6EFBB7" box="[1051,1275,1110,1131]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidotus zarudnyi</emphasis>
(Birula, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
, male neotype. 
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49361FBB9FB8CFB5F" bold="true" box="[1031,1049,1134,1155]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49341FBB9FA0FFB5F" authority="(Birula, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Birula" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1063,1434,1134,1155]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49341FBB9FB68FB5F" box="[1063,1277,1134,1155]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidotus gracilis</emphasis>
(Birula, 1900)
</taxonomicName>
, female holotype.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD8FFB49796F9C4FC05FACA" blockId="3.[192,802,1218,1916]" lastBlockId="3.[830,1441,1218,1916]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
Vachon, however, never published a new generic name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49653F9E5FE7FF995" authorityName="Birula" authorityYear="1900" box="[309,490,1586,1609]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Buthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zarudnyi">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49653F9E5FE7FF995" box="[309,490,1586,1609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Buthus zarudnyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Farzanpay (1988: 39, 40) listed the name (spelled with “th” as 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB495E4F986FC8EF9B4" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1988" box="[642,795,1617,1640]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidothus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB495E4F986FC8EF9B4" box="[642,795,1617,1640]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which constitutes an incorrect subsequent spelling) along with two other new scorpion genera, where he planned to be one of the authors: “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49525F97AFD33F918" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[579,678,1709,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Olivierus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49525F97AFD33F918" box="[579,678,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Olivierus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n. gen. to be described by Farzanpay &amp; Vachon),” “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB495FEF91CFD6FF93E" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[664,762,1739,1762]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Razianus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB495FEF91CFD6FF93E" box="[664,762,1739,1762]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Razianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n. gen. to be described by Vachon &amp; Farzanpay),” and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB497AAF8DEFEF0F8FC" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1988" box="[204,357,1801,1824]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidothus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB497AAF8DEFEF0F8FC" box="[204,357,1801,1824]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n. gen. to be described by Farzanpay &amp; Vachon)”. In the introduction, he wrote (Farzanpay, 1988: 34): “The new creations are based on the cooperation and suggestion of Professor Max Vachon of the Muséum national d´Histoire naturelle in Paris as agreed by personal communication. ...(letter 
<date id="FFC6107DFFD8FFB4924FFB36FCE6FACA" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" value="1984-08-30">August 30, 1984</date>
)”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD8FFB49408FAC9FC55F9D0" blockId="3.[830,1441,1218,1916]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
Unfortunately, no further descriptions of these genera by Vachon ever appeared until Vachon’s death in 1992; there is also no evidence that Vachon was aware that descriptions of three new genera and one new species were published by Farzanpay (1987). About 
<specimenCount id="9D7EFD34FFD8FFB492E3FA4EFC38FA12" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="generic">20 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36F762DFFD8FFB49489FA60FB8FFA12" box="[1007,1050,1463,1486]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Iran</collectingCountry>
labeled “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB493E6FA60FA8CFA12" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1988" box="[1152,1305,1463,1486]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidothus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB493E6FA60FA8CFA12" box="[1152,1305,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidothus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” by 
<location id="8EA76066FFD8FFB4922BFA60FA35FA12" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03D187ABFFD9FFB4962BF9AAFAE3F8A0:8EA76066FFD8FFB4922BFA60FA35FA12" box="[1357,1440,1463,1486]" country="Iran" name="Vachon" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Vachon</location>
exist in 
<collectionCode id="ED69AE78FFD8FFB494FEFA01FC7CFA31" box="[920,1001,1494,1517]" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">MNHN</collectionCode>
(pers. comm. from 
<collectorName id="268D536BFFD8FFB493A0FA01FA17FA31" box="[1222,1410,1494,1517]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Wilson Lourenço</collectorName>
to 
<collectorName id="268D536BFFD8FFB49458FA22FCF8F9D0" box="[830,877,1525,1548]" name="Victor Fet" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">V.F.</collectorName>
, 1996).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC736BDFFD8FFB49408F9C4FAE3F8A0" blockId="3.[830,1441,1218,1916]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49490F9C4FB14F9F6" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1014,1153,1555,1578]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49490F9C4FB14F9F6" box="[1014,1153,1555,1578]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was never revised, and therefore was considered valid by Fet &amp; Lowe (2000: 222), as well as other genera published in Farzanpay (1987), namely, 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB4949AF9B8FBCAF95A" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1020,1119,1647,1670]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Olivierus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4949AF9B8FBCAF95A" box="[1020,1119,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Olivierus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49312F9B8FB43F95A" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1140,1238,1647,1670]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Razianus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49312F9B8FB43F95A" box="[1140,1238,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Razianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49278F9B8FA0CF95A" box="[1310,1433,1647,1670]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Simonoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49278F9B8FA0CF95A" box="[1310,1433,1647,1670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Simonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The authorship of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB4933BF959FB55F979" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1117,1216,1678,1701]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Olivierus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4933BF959FB55F979" box="[1117,1216,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Olivierus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB4938AF959FADBF979" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[1260,1358,1678,1701]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Razianus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB4938AF959FADBF979" box="[1260,1358,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Razianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB49458F97AFC5CF918" authorityName="Farzanpay" authorityYear="1987" box="[830,969,1709,1732]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Sassanidotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB49458F97AFC5CF918" box="[830,969,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Sassanidotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, was assigned only to Farzanpay (1987) by Fet &amp; Lowe (2000: 189, 216, 222) since they did not think that Vachon was responsible for the descriptions (quite incomplete and inadequate) as published by Farzanpay (1987). On complicated authorship of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB494B9F891FBCFF881" box="[991,1114,1862,1885]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Simonoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB494B9F891FBCFF881" box="[991,1114,1862,1885]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Simonoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now confirmed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C784D3EFFD8FFB494A2F8B2FBD3F8A0" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1892" box="[964,1094,1893,1916]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90CEAAFFFD8FFB494A2F8B2FBD3F8A0" box="[964,1094,1893,1916]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Orthochirus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), see Kovařík &amp; Fet (2006).
</paragraph>
